article.headline: Yale 34, Dartmouth 7
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. -- Ryan Fodor threw two touchdown passes and Mike McLeod rushed for 135 yards and a touchdown to lead Yale to a 34-7 victory over injury-riddled Dartmouth on Saturday. The winless Big Green played without six starters and were held to 38 yards rushing. Fodor sat out the first scoring drive after being sidelined by a helmet-to-helmet hit on his third play of the game. Backup Brook Hart led Yale on an 80-yard scoring drive for the Bulldogs' first touchdown, a 12-yard pass to John Sheffield. It was the only series Fodor missed. His first scoring pass came one play after Tom McCarthy intercepted a Dartmouth pass at the Yale 40. Wide receiver Reid Lathan caught a pass that was tipped into the air to give Yale a 13-0 halftime lead. Paul Rice recovered a Dartmouth fumble early in the third quarter to lead to the next score, Fodor's 31-yard pass to Patrick Sedden. Dartmouth's only score came on Alex Jenny's 21-yard pass to Tim McManus. Yale took a 27-7 lead on McLeod's 2-yard touchdown run and Rice closed out the scoring when he intercepted a pass and returned it 24 yards for a touchdown.
